<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2"> 
      <tr> 
        <td width="100%" height="30" align="center" colspan="2" class="big" bgcolor="#A34D1E">Krziik the Mighty&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:content@gameznet.com?subject=Bestiary Info : Krziik the Mighty">Submit Info</a></font></td> 
      </tr> 
	  <tr bgcolor="#4A2A12"> 
	    <td align="left">

<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b>&nbsp;68-68<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font>&nbsp;Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font>&nbsp;Sub-Boss<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font>&nbsp;Reef of Coirnav<br>
  <br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font>
  <br>- Immune to Slow<br />
- Flurries<br />
- Rampages<br />
<br />
<b>Spawn and Scouting</b><br />
<br />
Krziik the Mighty can be tracked from near Hydrotha. There are two Triloun Champions who patrol the tunnels just before the pathway down where he becomes in tracking range. You will need to wait around and time when you can move past them. <br />
<br />
He is a three day spawn.<br />
<br />
<b>What You Need</b><br />
<br />
Krziik the Mighty can be killed with 45ish players. There are no AEs or special attacks to deal with. It is straight up melee fight with rampage. He hits hard though and is unslowable. <br />
<br />
You will need at least two good tanks, and I would recommend more in case the main tank dies. You will need at minimum 6 clerics, and I'd recommend 8+. Other than that just add DPS as you can. <br />
<br />
<b>Getting to the Pull Location</b><br />
<br />
If you do not know how to reach Krziik the Mighty then I would refer you to <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqmap1&eqzones.zone_name=%22Reef%20of%20Coirnav%22">this map</a>. You can invis down to the prep area but there are two Triloun Champions which spawn in the tunnels on the way down. They like to pause in one place for minutes at a time, which makes this frustrating. If you kill the two champions then it is easy to invis down to the second tunnel down past Hydrotha if Hydrotha is not up. After that you will encounter Regrua who will see invis. You must fight in from there.<br />
<br />
You can also COTH down, which is a common method.<br />
<br />
<b>Preparation</b><br />
<br />
Be sure that all of your tanks have some form of levitation. This will prevent them from dropping down as they are idle in the water. Everyone should also be wearing a water breathing item, or have the spell cast on them. <br />
<br />
Aside from this there are no surprises to this fight. It is a straight up melee encounter.<br />
<br />
<b>The Fight</b><br />
<br />
Krziik the Mighty is a fight that relies primarily on tanking power. He hits for ~2500 per attack, but is immune to slow. He flurries and rampages. He has no AE or special attacks, however.<br />
<br />
You will need a 6+ cleric healing chain and to have at least two more casters dedicated to keeping the rampage tank alive. If you have the clerics I would recommend placing a three cleric chain on the rampage tank.<br />
<br />
He does not rampage as often, or hit as hard as Magmaton in the Plane of Fire. The fight is othwerise similar though. Keep your tanks alive and it's an easy win. If you don't have well geared (9500 hp+) tanks then this encounter is going to give you fits. <br />
<br />
<b>Loot</b><br />
<br />
Krziik the Mighty drops two loots per kill. He can drop elemental bracer and sleeves molds. Also in his loot table is a 43/37 4 cold damage bow with a manatap proc and a 33/22 pal/shd 1HSlash with a Runic proc. <br />
<br />
In addition to these loots he can also drop runes and spectral parchments.<br><br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=12005" alt="Ornate Abalone Recurve Bow">Ornate Abalone Recurve Bow</a><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=12249" alt="Gem Encrusted Axe">Gem Encrusted Axe</a><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=14028" alt="Elemental Leather Bracelet Pattern">Elemental Leather Bracelet Pattern</a><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=15167" alt="Elemental Silk Bracer Pattern">Elemental Silk Bracer Pattern</a><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="item.php?id=15172" alt="Elemental Chain Bracelet Pattern">Elemental Chain Bracelet Pattern</a><br>  
<br><b>Related Quests</b>:<br>
  
